               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office prayers and litanies (fols. 3ra-23va)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse "Ordinary of the Mass" (fols. 23va-48vb)
 III) Anaphoras (fols.
                     49ra-132rb)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 49va-61vb
 III-2)
                     Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 62ra-66ra)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our
                     Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 66rb-76va)
 III-4) Anaphora of St
                     John, son of Thunder (fols. 76vb-86rb)
 III-5) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox
                     Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 86rb-93va)
 III-6) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom
                     (fols. 93va-98ra)
 III-7) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus (fols.
                     98rb-103vb)
 III-8) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 103vb-109va)
                     III-9) Anaphora of St Gregory of Armenia ("Hosanna-liturgy of St Gregory")
                     (fols. 109va-115rb)
 III-10) Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols.
                     115va-124ra)
 III-11) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of Alexandria
                     (fols.124ra-126vb)
 III-12) Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols.
                     126vb-132rb)
 
 Additio 1.</summary>
